### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe the problem.

I'm writing a function to dynamically build the route for my controller's action in a Blazor WebAssembly application and also get strong typed controllers / actions method names in my development experience.
I already can do this, except if I try to return `ActionResult` in my controllers.

For example: This is the controller in the `Server` project:
```cs
[ApiController]
[Route("[controller]/[action]")]
public class WeatherForecastController : ControllerBase, IWeatherForecastController
{
    public ActionResult<List<string>> GetList()
    {
        return new List<string>();
    }
}
```

This is the interface in the `Shared` project:
```cs
public interface IWeatherForecastController
{
    ActionResult<List<string>> GetList();
}
```

According to this and [this](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/26724), and [this](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/27373), this is not possible because I can't refer MVC binaries from a Blazor WebAssembly.

The current workaround I'm using is that my controllers return my own specific implementation of `ActionResult`.

### Describe the solution you'd like

To create a library like `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Abstractions` that can be referenced by both Blazor WebAssembly and by the Hosted Server.

